Subject: XSS Vulnerability in EnanoCms 1.1.7 & 1.1.6

Information
--------------------
Name :  XSS vulnerability in EnanoCms
Software :  All versions prior to and including 1.1.7 and 1.0.6 are affected.
Vendor Hompeage :  http://www.enanocms.org
Vulnerability Type :  Cross-Site Scripting
Severity :  High
Researcher :  Mesut Timur <mesut [at] mavitunasecurity [dot] com>
Advisory Reference :  NS-11-002

Description
------------------
EnanoCMS is a new, innovative CMS concept designed to be flexible and
user-friendly. From the reliable and solid core to its beautiful,
responsive user interface, Enano has everything you expect from
today's content management framework.

Details
-------------------
Enano is affected by a XSS vulnerability in all versions prior to and
including 1.1.7 and 1.0.6.
You can read the full article about Cross-Site Scripting
vulnerabilities from here :
http://www.mavitunasecurity.com/crosssite-scripting-xss/

Solution
-------------------
Upgrade to the latest EnanoCMS version (1.1.7pl1 and 1.0.6pl2 or later).

Credits
-------------------
It has been discovered on testing of Netsparker, Web Application
Security Scanner - http://www.mavitunasecurity.com/netsparker/.

References
-------------------
1. Vendor URL: http://enanocms.org/News:Article/2010/06/28/Enano_1.0.6pl2_and_1.1.7pl1_released
2. MSL Advisory Link :
http://www.mavitunasecurity.com/XSS-vulnerability-in-EnanoCms
3. Netsparker Advisories :
http://www.mavitunasecurity.com/netsparker-advisories/

